signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Shutdown defenders have the talent to erase receivers from the game. When they enter the zone, their coverage is tighter and interceptions are more frequent on contested catches.
Defenders with this ability don't allow broken tackles when hit-sticking ballcarriers - regardless of the runner's size or power.
Some pass rushers intimidate quarterbacks with their sheer presence. When they enter the zone, they can apply significant pressure on quarterbacks even while engaged with blockers.
Defenders with this ability use dominant pass rush moves while rushing from the edge of the defense.
Freight Trains are relentless runners who refuse to go down on first contact. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance to break the next tackle.
Passers with this ability are faster and more responsive to user input while scrambling behind the line of scrimmage.
Passers with this ability immediately respond to user input (and defenders react more slowly) on designed quarterback run plays.
While in the pocket, passers with this ability are almost guaranteed to break the first sack attempt by a blitzing defensive back.
